          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Instructions"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "e8659b31-290c-494f-adb8-d0ece413e534",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "1 Prepare Pork Shoulder Meat: Remove rind and bone from the pork shoulder meat. Cut pork shoulder meat into cubes (~2 inches). Keep the excess fat."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "f8cef7fb-ff28-459f-8133-90d3d964c362",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "2 Marinate Pork Shoulder Cubes:"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "c431d422-c34f-4850-9c49-b94c65360b4e",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Place pork shoulder cubes & fat into the Instant Pot\u2019s inner pot. Season very generously with kosher salt and ground black pepper. Add 4 crushed garlic cloves, chopped onion, 1 tsp (2g) ground cumin, 1 tsp (2g) cinnamon powder, 2 bay leaves, 1 tbsp (15ml) regular soy sauce, and juice (55ml) from 1 orange to the inner pot. Mix well and let the meat marinate for 20 minutes."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "a9ffbb62-cc25-4388-8a41-f156c425e7dd",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "3 Pressure Cook Pork Shoulder Cubes: Pour ~\u2158 cup (200ml) unsalted chicken stock in the inner pot. Close lid and Pressure Cook at High Pressure for 30 minutes + 15 minutes Natural Release. Release the remaining pressure after 15 minutes and open the lid carefully."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "5ed9d822-0d78-4759-8ea4-745002d19168",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "4 Crisp Pork Shoulder Cubes: Transfer the pork shoulder cubes onto a baking tray. Now is a good time to take a bite and see if the pork cubes are salty enough. If the pork cubes are not salty enough, add more kosher salt into the cooking liquid. Taste & adjust accordingly."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "1a83466f-7ab3-4259-a64d-b7567d7208d4",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Drizzle some of the cooking liquid on to each piece (The cooking liquid should be mostly fat. If not, mix \u00bc cup (63ml) cooking liquid with 2 tbsp (30ml) of vegetable oil and drizzle over each piece of pork). The fat & oil will protect the meat from drying out and the surface will crisp faster."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "b2811cf1-fe28-459f-ac64-c75afd7b254d",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Place pork shoulder cubes under a broiler or the top rack of a preheated 450\u00b0F toaster oven until the surface is crisped. Roughly 8 \u2013 10 minutes. Flip the pork shoulder cubes, drizzle each piece with more cooking liquid and place in the oven again until the surface is crisped."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "f69ac8b8-e996-4bb1-b689-7a23fb6447ef",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "5 (Optional) Heat Corn Tortillas: If you are serving the Carnitas with corned tortillas, you can heat up the corn tortillas when the pork is browning in the oven."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "fd52cd7e-92c0-46c4-8d62-cfda4cae6b63",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "6 Serve & Enjoy: Place piping hot Carnitas on top of the warmed corn tortillas with a spoonful of salsa (Pico De Gallo). Serve immediately!"
        }
      ],
